	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes shaman are the best all a round class :)<br>what did you expect? After all this is the shaman board.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Since you didn't define all-a-round, I will.  It is the ability to solo, the ability to get into a group, it is the ability to melee and to kill with magic.  If you can do these four things then you are an all-a-round class.  <br>Of course the first two are the most important.  <br>Necros, Mages, Shaman and Druids, are the four best soloing classes.  Of these four, only druids and shaman are regulary sought by pick-up groups.  <br>For this reason and because you menctioned druids I'll limit my comparission to these two.  <br><br>Soloing <br>I give the advantage to the shaman.  This will surprise some of you.  After all the druid is know for thir soloing, or should I say kiting.  And yes no-one can kite like a druid.  And yes druids can lvl up quicky with their kitting ability.  However if a shaman melee solo or pet solos, after pet lvl they can kill many places that druids can't.  Shaman can solo in some dongens, and in other places where it is impossible to kite, and thus can obtain better items, more plat, and even exp during high use times when mobs to kite can be hard to find. <br><br>Grouping<br>Durids and shaman have a number of comman abilities that make them desirable in a group.  SOW and healing.  However the shaman can slow, which at higher lvl is very important.  They can also speed up the melee class and cast other useful buffs, wich are better than those cast by druids.  For these reasons Shaman have an easyer time getting into groups.  <br><br>Melee<br>Shaman have better armor and higher damage weapons than druids and thus can melee better.  Shaman also get pets, wich give extra melee punch to any group.  <br><br>Killing with mana<br>Durids tend to have higher wisdome and thus more mana, and are there for better at killing with just mana. <br><br>So the shaman wins 3 out of 4... and is therefore the better all-around class.    <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
