	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99606694246264><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99606694246264>RE: Called a Ninja Looter</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99606694246264#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=6988><span id=Scholar>Badjur</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>93 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jul 25th 9:15 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>In an hour and a half, you might kill as many as 50 mobs in Seb.&nbsp;&nbsp;So if you looted only 4, I hardly call that being a loot hog.<br><br>The cleric was wrong to ask for the gems. Fire Opals aren't even a cleric spell component, and with FFA loot, the cleric had his/her own opportunity to FFA loot.  (btw, I've been in a group in Seb where the chanter consistently begged for all the gems that dropped because he was a jewel crafter).<br><br>As far as cleric covering expenses in a group, it is good practice for everyone to pack a few jaspers (about a plat each) and a peridot or two.   I hate seeing people begging for Symbol over and over  throughout the course of a grouping, but make no offer to the cleric to compensate him/her for the gem.  <br><br>Good rule of thumb is that if you ask a cleric for Symbol, be prepared to cough up a peridot or 11pp, and if you ask for Death Pact, be prepared to cough up a pearl of 5pp.  That's it.  You are not responsible for supplying all the gems for her raids.<br><br>As for loot rules in Seb, they vary.  Most generally it's FFA and NBG (need before greed)  I wouldn't say that a fire opal falls in the NBG category for a cleric.  For the most part, the only gems rolled on are diamonds and blue diamonds, and many groups opt to only roll for blue diamonds.  Loot rules vary a bit with each group, so get informed prior to heading into Seb.  If you don't like the loot rules for that group, try and come to a compromise.  If you still aren't happy, then find another group (which I don't really recommend...groups in Seb can be hard to find). <br><br>You sold Fire Opals to a merchant??!!!  Shame on you!  LOL  Invest a bit of plat (about 280pp)  in them.  Have a master jeweler (skill 250 if possible) work them up in velium.  The finished product sells for about 700pp.  Can't complain about a 420pp profit  :)<br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>Oracle of Novus Invictus<br>(Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>51 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
